text: Vlada Anatolyevna Chernyavskaya (, ; born 10 June 1966) is a Belarusian badminton player. She competed in women's singles and mixed doubles at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1966 births Category:Living people Category:Belarusian female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Belarus Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics
